de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.searchAlgorithms
Interface SearchAlgorithm

All Known Implementing Classes:
DepthFirstSearchAlgorithm, IterativeDeepeningSearchAlgorithm
public interface SearchAlgorithm

This interface is implemented by any class that offers a search algorithm. It specifies the methods there classes have to offer, so that the search algorithm can be used in the symbolic execution of a program. Especially the backtracking functionality is of importance.

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-08-29
Author:
Tim Majchrzak

getCurrentChoicePoint

ChoicePoint getCurrentChoicePoint()
Get the current ChoicePoint of this search algorithm. It reflects the last node in the searching tree visited.

Returns:
The current choice point.

trackBack

boolean trackBack(SymbolicVirtualMachine vm)
Execution has reached a solution or a point where further execution should not take part (at least for the moment). This method will track back according to the search algorithm implemented, setting the SymbolicalVirtualMachine to the state of the ChoicePoint tracked back to.

Parameters:
vm - The currently executing SymbolicalVirtualMachine.
Returns:
true, if tracking back was successfull and the execution can be continued, false, if there was no possibility for tracking back and then execution should hence be stopped.

generateNewChoicePoint

void generateNewChoicePoint(SymbolicVirtualMachine vm,
                            int localVariableIndex,
                            Generator generator)
                            throws ConversionException,
                                   SymbolicExecutionException
Generate a new GeneratorChoicePoint or ArrayInitializationChoicePoint for a local variable. Set it as the current choice point and mark that the jumping branch has been visited already (since execution just continues there.)

Parameters:
vm - The currently executing SymbolicalVirtualMachine.
localVariableIndex - The index into the local variable table to store the generated array at.
generator - A variable Generator. May be null to indicate no custom variable generator is used.
Throws:
ConversionException - If converting the first provided object failed.
SymbolicExecutionException - If a type is encountered that no array can be created for.

generateNewChoicePoint

void generateNewChoicePoint(SymbolicVirtualMachine vm,
                            CompareFp instruction,
                            boolean less,
                            de.wwu.testtool.expressions.Term leftTerm,
                            de.wwu.testtool.expressions.Term rightTerm)
                            throws SymbolicExecutionException
Generate a new FpComparisonChoicePoint. Set it as the current choice point.

Parameters:
vm - The currently executing SymbolicalVirtualMachine.
instruction - The Instruction generating the ChoicePoint.
less - If set to true, the choice point will have the behaviour of dcmpl / fcmpl; otherwise, it will behave like dcmpg / fcmpg.
leftTerm - The term of long variables and constants of the left hand side of the comparison.
rightTerm - The term of long variables and constants of the right hand side of the comparison.
Throws:
SymbolicExecutionException - If an Exception is thrown during the choice point generation.

generateNewChoicePoint

void generateNewChoicePoint(SymbolicVirtualMachine vm,
                            Switch instruction,
                            de.wwu.testtool.expressions.Term termFromStack,
                            de.wwu.testtool.expressions.IntConstant[] keys,
                            int[] pcs,
                            de.wwu.testtool.expressions.IntConstant low,
                            de.wwu.testtool.expressions.IntConstant high)
                            throws SymbolicExecutionException
Generate a new SwitchingComparisonChoicePoint. Set it as the current choice point.

Parameters:
vm - The currently executing SymbolicalVirtualMachine.
instruction - The Instruction generating the ChoicePoint.
termFromStack - The term term that was on top of the stack. Using the non symbolic execution, this would be the key for the switch.
keys - The possible keys.
pcs - The possible jump targets.
low - The "low" boundary of the tableswitch instruction; or null, if the choice point is generated for a lookupswitch instruction.
high - The "high" boundary of the tableswitch instruction; or null, if the choice point is generated for a lookupswitch instruction.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the number of keys is not equal to the number of jump targets or if there are no choices at all.
java.lang.NullPointerException - If either of the specified arrays is null, or if the instruction is tableswitch and at least one of the boundaries is null.
SymbolicExecutionException - If an Exception is thrown during the choice point generation.

getStatisticalInformation

java.lang.String[][] getStatisticalInformation()
Return statistical information about the execution. The information is returned as an two-dimensional String array. Its first dimension represents the distinct statistical informations that can be supplied. The second dimension has two elements. Element 0 is the name of the statistical criterion, element 1 is the string representation of its value.

Returns:
Statistical information about the execution.
